<P><HI>When [readers were not many]</HI> we were not yet a nation of readers.</P>
<P>[Every man who] <HI>he that could &s;ay he</HI> knew him.</P>
<P>Every man of known influence has &s;o many [more] petitions [than] <HI>which</HI> he [can] <HI>cannot</HI> grant, that he mu&s;t nece&s;&s;arily offend more than he [can gratify] <HI>gratifies.</HI></P>
<P>Eccle&s;ia&s;tical [preferments] <HI>benefices.</HI></P>
